children.name: BMC Support
children.description: Enable/Disable interfaces to communicate with BMC

children.name: IPMI Interface Type
children.description: Type of Interface to communicate BMC from HOST

children.name: Wait For BMC
children.description: Wait For BMC response for specified time out. In PILOTII, BMC starts at the same time when BIOS starts during AC power ON. It takes around 30 seconds to initialize Host to BMC interfaces.

children.name: FRB-2 Timer
children.description: Enable or Disable FRB-2 timer(POST timer)

children.name: FRB-2 Timer timeout
children.description: Enter value Between 1 to 30 min for FRB-2 Timer Expiration

children.name: FRB-2 Timer Policy
children.description: Configure how the system should respond if the FRB-2 Timer expires. Not available if FRB-2 Timer is disabled.

children.name: OS Watchdog Timer
children.description: If enabled, starts a BIOS timer which can only be shut off by Management Software after the OS loads.  Helps determine that the OS successfully loaded or follows the OS Boot Watchdog Timer policy.

children.name: OS Wtd Timer Timeout
children.description: Enter the value Between 1 to 30 min for OS Boot Watchdog Timer Expiration. Not available if OS Boot Watchdog Timer is disabled.

children.name: OS Wtd Timer Policy
children.description: Configure how the system should respond if the OS Boot Watchdog Timer expires. Not available if OS Boot Watchdog Timer is disabled.
